Since there is no universal answer, we will
also discuss how to choose between various

5
00:00:24,080 --> 00:00:28,869
management systems and identify good and bad
practices.

6
00:00:28,869 --> 00:00:32,570
Medical Waste Management can be divided in
five main stages:

7
00:00:32,570 --> 00:00:37,350
The first stage is the Segregation:
The sorting of the waste in the established

8
00:00:37,350 --> 00:00:42,739
categories must always be the responsibility
of the person who produce it.

9
00:00:42,739 --> 00:00:45,089
Usually a clinical staff member.

10
00:00:45,089 --> 00:00:49,699
Ideally as soon as the waste is produced,
it has to be disposed.

11
00:00:49,699 --> 00:00:54,239
It must be done as close as possible to the
site where the waste is produced.

12
00:00:54,239 --> 00:00:59,390
Of course, it worthy to mention that if the
waste is separated it means that the treatment

13
00:00:59,390 --> 00:01:00,390
will be different.

14
00:01:00,390 --> 00:01:06,170
There is no point in sorting wastes that eventually
undergoes the same treatment process.

15
00:01:06,170 --> 00:01:11,930
The second stage is the Temporary Storage:
Waste must be collected regularly.

16
00:01:11,930 --> 00:01:15,940
It must never be allowed to accumulate where
it is produced.

17
00:01:15,940 --> 00:01:20,119
The volume , the capacity of the containers,
and the frequency of collection are the main

18
00:01:20,119 --> 00:01:22,110
parameters to account.

19
00:01:22,110 --> 00:01:25,579
The third stage is the Transport
…to the waste area: The waste are separated

20
00:01:25,579 --> 00:01:28,659
in categories is transported to the waste
area.

21
00:01:28,659 --> 00:01:35,450
In a way that reduces the possibility of accidents
such as spillages for example

22
00:01:35,450 --> 00:01:40,979
The fourth stage is the Treatment:
According to the system in place, the waste

23
00:01:40,979 --> 00:01:43,552
need to be reduced in volume or made not hazardous
anymore.

24
00:01:43,552 --> 00:01:49,560
To reduce the public health risk such treatment
should be the responsibility of hospital and

25
00:01:49,560 --> 00:01:50,560
done on site.

26
00:01:50,560 --> 00:01:53,299
If no appropriate treatment infrastructure
exists in the vicinity.

27
00:01:53,299 --> 00:01:54,329
Finally, the disposal.

28
00:01:54,329 --> 00:01:55,900
The final and definitive step.

29
00:01:55,900 --> 00:02:02,859
Usually it consists in buring it in a sanitary
landfill or in waste pit.

